Roles & Responsibilities
We are Datadog's in-house product experts. The partner technical solutions team contributes to Datadog's worldwide growth by enabling our partner ecosystem to deliver value for our customers. Our mission is to build a highly skilled partner community for customers. We share our technical and product expertise with partners through demos, presentations, workshops, and ongoing support. Partner Technical Solutions is a growing global team continuously advancing our technical skillset. The Partner SAs are trusted technical advisors for our Partner channel. This role is a player/coach who will retain some individual contributor responsibilities along with management responsibilities outlined below.

At Datadog, we place value in our office culture - the relationships and collaboration it builds, and the creativity it brings to the table. We operate as a hybrid workplace to ensure our Datadogs can create a work-life harmony that best fits them.

What You Will Do:
Your team will own the development and execution of our strategy for the technical development of APAC partners to meet the needs of our business in the region;
Oversee a small team of individual contributors in the role of a coach, conduct 1:1s weekly, regular team meetings, and bi-annual performance feedback with each team member. Track and manage team member scheduling, utilization and productivity;
Participate regularly in recruiting for the team and across the organization and collaborate with leadership and team members on learning and development needs;
Lead partner-facing meetings or shadow team member work when appropriate and source feedback from partners that your team directly engages with;
Partner with Sales teams on account strategies for product expansion or partner enablement;
Collaborate with cross-functional leaders (Sales, Customer Customer Success, Product Management, Marketing, Support, Presales, Partners, etc) for internal and external initiatives;
Be involved with and lead at multiple OKR efforts annually while coordinating and delegating efforts across your team members;.
Who You Are:
You have a solid technical grounding with hands-on experience of IT Development and/or Operations with a demonstrable track-record and passion for learning; successful candidates for this position typically have 10-15 years of experience in a customer or partner facing technical role plus 1-3 years in a management role;
A curious self-starter, tech-savvy professional with solid business acumen; ability to articulate Datadog value from server room to boardroom;
Confident presentation skills; fluency in English required if not a native speaker;
Desired hands-on experience in four or more of the following areas:
Observability: Datadog, Splunk, AppD, New Relic or Dynatrace
Public Cloud: AWS, Azure, GCP, or Alibaba
Containerization: Docker, Kubernetes, OpenShift, Cloud Foundry
Dev/Scripting: Python, Javascript, Ruby, Perl, PHP, Go
Config Mgmt: Terraform, Ansible, Puppet, Chef
CI / CD: Jenkins, Gitlab
Previous experience working in a technical role for or supporting channel partners (Systems Integrators, Managed Services Providers, e.g.);
Previous experience with customer or partner success
Datadog values people from all walks of life. We understand not everyone will meet all the above qualifications on day one. That's okay. If you’re passionate about technology and want to grow your skills, we encourage you to apply.

Benefits and Growth:
Contribute to the development and growth of our indirect business;
Generous global benefits;
Intra-departmental mentor and buddy program for in-house networking;
New hire stock equity (RSUs) and employee stock purchase plan (ESPP);
Continuous professional development, product training, and career pathing;
Benefits and Growth listed above may vary based on the country of your employment and the nature of your employment with Datadog.

Roles & Responsibilities
· Must have experience in the Financial Industry (CIB and/or Wealth Management), exposure to both Buy Side or Sell Side Capital markets exposure will be beneficial;
· Business facing Analyst, with significant experience in Capital Markets, who has preferably worked with Front-Office stakeholders as well as all actors of the front-to-back chain;
· Good Knowledge of Financial and Global Market Regulations;
· Strong analytical and product management skills required, including a thorough understanding of how to interpret customer business needs and translate them into application and operational requirements;
· Good knowledge of Capital Markets and associated Front-to-Back chains, with at least one of two areas of functional expertise:
o Equity Structured products, Cash FX and FX Derivatives Products/Markets;
o Cash Equities and Equity Derivatives Products/Markets;
o Interest Rates and Credit Products/Markets - IRDs and Structured products;
o Funds / ETFs;
· Good understanding of Finance Technology, ability to work with Developers and Architecture teams;
· Knowledge of Trading, Middle Office and BackOffice platforms such as Bloomberg, Avaloq, FinIQ …, will be beneficial;
· Good vendor management skills;
· Project Management: especially Agile methodology
Other soft skills required:
· Excellent interpersonal skills: good negotiation and conflicts management skills, able to build momentum / define consensus.
· Excellent verbal and written communication skills and the ability to interact professionally with a diverse group, managers, and subject matter experts. Be able to adapt to the interlocutor.
· Structured, organized and results oriented approach, demonstrating a high level of diligence and attention to detail and the ability to ensure high quality and consistency in the deliverables produced;
· Ability to manage relationship with other business stakeholders, COO Office, Business Integrity & Control Functions along with IT teams (users, development, architecture, integration)
· Ability to multi task, be flexible and allocate time according to moving priorities.

Roles & Responsibilities
Job Description:
1. Design the crypto asset trading products of spot, margin, futures, perpetual swap and options, including the back-end service, user experience and new business mode, participating the whole life cycle of products from establishment to launch;
2. Provide the short and medium-term product iteration plan and RoadMap based on the life cycle characteristics of the product, competition environment and resource structure.
3. Collect product feedback from internal and external sources, optimize the product plan through qualitative or quantitative analysis methods;
4. Monitor the project progress and coordinate with developers, designers, market team, operation team and other departments.
5. Conduct the analysis of competing products and industry trends, and transform the valuable analysis to product iteration plan.

Job Requirements:
1. Have a strong interest in blockchain and the financial industry;
2. Possess rigorous logical thinking, excellent teamwork awareness and communication skills, and be able to organize and coordinate resources to solve problems and achieve goals between different departments;
3. Be proactive, enthusiastic, responsible to users and the team;
4. Experience in designing or trading financial products such as stocks, funds, forex, futures, options is preferred;
5. Having in-depth insight based on data analysis, with extensive experience using Excel, SQL, Python and other tools for data processing and analysis is preferred

